   given by

and similarly for multiplication. Such function spaces occur in many geometric situations, when Œ© is the real line or an interval, or other subsets of R. Many notions in topology and analysis, such as continuity, integrability or differentiability are well-behaved with respect to linearity: sums and scalar multiples of functions possessing such a property still have that property.  Therefore, the set of such functions are vector spaces, whose study belongs to functional analysis.

